metadata.description: This extract from 246a to 248c of Plato's Phaedrus describes the nature of the soul as a power composed of a celestial winged carriage in order to participate in the celestial march.
metadata.keywords: Phaedrus, Plato, 246a-248c, celestial winged chariot, nature of the soul
metadata.imageTitle: Plato, Phaedrus, the celestial winged chariot
metadata.imageLegend: Several powers composed by celestial winged carriages participate in the celestial walk.
